JOHANNESBURG, May 1 (ANA) – The South African Federation of Trade Unions (SAFTU) has announced that it will be holding May Day rallies across the country starting at 10 am. The union federation said its main rally will be held in Bloemfontein at the Vista Arena, University of the Free State. SAFTU President Mac Chavalala will address the rally. In Durban, SAFTU members will assemble at Botha’s Place and march to the City Hall, where SAFTU 1st Deputy President Nomvume Ralarala will address them. SAFTU National Treasurer Motswari Letshogo will address union members at the Ngoako Sports centre in Seshego.